# VERSION
v0.2.0

# Changelog
- v0.2.0
    - Implement full Atlas Knowledge Graph Engine backend
    - **Architecture: Neo4j access via PhoenixA data middleware**
        - Atlas does NOT connect to Neo4j directly (same pattern as PostgreSQL via phoenixA)
        - All graph read/write operations go through PhoenixA's /api/v1/graph/* endpoints
        - neo4j_client.py rewritten as thin compatibility shim delegating to phoenixa_client
        - Removed neo4j Python driver dependency from pyproject.toml
    - Add PhoenixA integration: replace direct PostgreSQL with phoenixa_client HTTP connector
    - Add phoenixa_client graph methods: run_cypher, merge_node/edge (single + batch), search, company/event queries
    - Add MinIO S3 connector for document storage
    - Add RSS news fetcher connector
    - Add event dedup service with fingerprint-based deduplication (Layer 2)
    - Add impact rules engine with deterministic rule-based scoring
    - Add graph builder service with quality gate — writes via phoenixa_client batch merge
    - Add graph query service — reads via phoenixa_client graph endpoints
    - Add company review service with LLM-generated investment analysis
    - Add extraction API endpoints (trigger + query)
    - Add web-clip API endpoint for browser bookmarklet
    - Add events, daily-runs, impact-logs query endpoints
    - Update daily pipeline with event dedup + graph builder integration
    - Update documents API to use phoenixA + MinIO persistence
    - Update graph API — all functions async, use phoenixa_client
    - Update config: add taxonomy, minio, DeepSeek V4 model config
    - Update graph_schema: extended EventType and SourceType enums
    - Add Cthulhu frontend Atlas feature module:
        - Dashboard: graph stats, recent events, daily runs
        - Graph Explorer: ECharts supply chain visualization
        - Events & Impact: event list, LLM impact analysis
        - Company Review: LLM-generated investment review
        - Document Management: upload, list, extract
    - Add unit tests:
        - test_event_dedup: 9 tests (fingerprint + time bucket)
        - test_impact_rules: 15 tests (scoring + rules + propagation)
        - test_ingestion: 9 tests (hash, chunking, text extraction)
        - test_graph_schema: 6 tests (model validation + enums)
        - test_phoenixa_graph: 12 tests (graph HTTP client mocks)
        - test_graph_builder: 10 tests (quality gate + node props + label resolution)
        - test_neo4j_client: 5 tests (PhoenixA delegation shim)
- v0.1.0
    - Review design of Atlas and make necessary adjustments.
- v0.0.1
    - Init atlas